    {
      "text": "A 59-year-old man with hepatitis C cirrhosis presents with acute onset of diffuse abdominal pain. Vital signs are BP, 102/64 mm Hg; P, 116; R, 20; T, 37.7°C (99.9°F). Examination shows abdominal tenderness, tense ascites, and mild jaundice. Laboratory studies show WBC 11,800/mm3, platelets 95 × 103/mm3, INR 1.3, AST 82 U/L, ALT 60 U/L, bilirubin 3.2 mg/dL, albumin 3.0 g/dL. Diagnostic paracentesis shows clear fluid with WBC 200/mm3 (25% neutrophils), protein 2.3 g/dL, albumin 1.5 g/dL. Bedside Doppler ultrasound is shown. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Initiate systemic anticoagulation and consult hepatology"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Administer intravenous broad-spectrum antibiotics"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Start nonselective beta-blocker therapy to reduce portal hypertension"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Arrange emergent transjugular intrahepatic portosystemic shunt (TIPS) placement"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Provide supportive care and monitor for spontaneous resolution"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Correct – The cornerstone of acute <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=DG01Y3&anker=Z8d98d30e81cf30f314ef8a92ef5d6e8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"DG01Y3\" data-anker=\"Z8d98d30e81cf30f314ef8a92ef5d6e8e\" data-sememe-id=\"l9Yvnr\">portal vein thrombosis</a> management is anticoagulation to prevent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z1791adcca5dde6a721a3f09928e106be\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z1791adcca5dde6a721a3f09928e106be\" data-section-id=\"X619j30\" data-sememe-id=\"KS1U0g0\">thrombus</a> propagation and complications of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LS0wZf&anker=Zd5beacd46243f9dbc75a7032728717a5\" data-learningcard-id=\"LS0wZf\" data-anker=\"Zd5beacd46243f9dbc75a7032728717a5\" data-sememe-id=\"A40RNT\">portal hypertension</a>. Further management should be guided by specialists. </div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=GM0BJg&anker=Z4fb9a359446298e0b5912478808dc7e5\" data-learningcard-id=\"GM0BJg\" data-anker=\"Z4fb9a359446298e0b5912478808dc7e5\" data-sememe-id=\"QE0uv3\">Spontaneous bacterial peritonitis</a> (<span data-sememe-id=\"mucV7V0\">SBP</span>) is diagnosed when ascitic fluid has ≥250 <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ln0vtg&anker=Zbd116a28cc685c0061df7ed2c2332da1\" data-learningcard-id=\"ln0vtg\" data-anker=\"Zbd116a28cc685c0061df7ed2c2332da1\" data-section-id=\"nac7Oa0\" data-sememe-id=\"F6bg5u\">polymorphonuclear leukocytes</a>/mm3. This patient’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=PF0WR3&anker=Z298f094c80caa2931a43acdefb33db7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"PF0WR3\" data-anker=\"Z298f094c80caa2931a43acdefb33db7b\" data-sememe-id=\"qRbCLt\">paracentesis</a> shows only 200 <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ln0vtg&anker=Z18a02873023ccef6d8ea2b461e0b7446\" data-learningcard-id=\"ln0vtg\" data-anker=\"Z18a02873023ccef6d8ea2b461e0b7446\" data-section-id=\"5aciOa0\" data-sememe-id=\"86bO5u\">WBC</a>/mm3 with 25% <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ln0vtg&anker=Zd36074c54a3f63afa3afea2a3d7d26db\" data-learningcard-id=\"ln0vtg\" data-anker=\"Zd36074c54a3f63afa3afea2a3d7d26db\" data-section-id=\"nac7Oa0\" data-sememe-id=\"DMb1I8\">neutrophils</a>, which is below the diagnostic threshold for <span data-sememe-id=\"mucV7V0\">SBP</span>. In addition, the key imaging finding is absent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zf755e99eca186a2dfdaa32b290e1ba0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zf755e99eca186a2dfdaa32b290e1ba0f\" data-section-id=\"Z8cZOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"VjXGzB\">portal venous</a> flow due to <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombosis</span>, which requires a different treatment.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uN0p1g&anker=Zb77d4775f43042430e3f648be46490e9\" data-learningcard-id=\"uN0p1g\" data-anker=\"Zb77d4775f43042430e3f648be46490e9\" data-section-id=\"RrblSE\" data-sememe-id=\"oRa0L4\">Nonselective beta-blockers</a> are used for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Zs0Zth&anker=Z3b12fcfa63d3f70fa0fc718640d0af94\" data-learningcard-id=\"Zs0Zth\" data-anker=\"Z3b12fcfa63d3f70fa0fc718640d0af94\" data-section-id=\"OjWI0l0\" data-sememe-id=\"UE0bE3\">variceal bleeding</a> prophylaxis in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=PS0W-2&anker=Za99be06553ff299396a513bb65ed71be\" data-learningcard-id=\"PS0W-2\" data-anker=\"Za99be06553ff299396a513bb65ed71be\" data-sememe-id=\"D401lT\">cirrhosis</a> but do not address acute <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombotic</span> obstruction. They have no role in the immediate management of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=DG01Y3&anker=Z8d98d30e81cf30f314ef8a92ef5d6e8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"DG01Y3\" data-anker=\"Z8d98d30e81cf30f314ef8a92ef5d6e8e\" data-sememe-id=\"l9Yvnr\">portal vein thrombosis</a> in the emergency setting.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LS0wZf&anker=Z968cf3fc530ed473c421f64ebc82fae2\" data-learningcard-id=\"LS0wZf\" data-anker=\"Z968cf3fc530ed473c421f64ebc82fae2\" data-section-id=\"N_0-oi\" data-sememe-id=\"fE0kE3\">TIPS</a> can be considered in refractory or chronic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=DG01Y3&anker=Z8d98d30e81cf30f314ef8a92ef5d6e8e\" data-learningcard-id=\"DG01Y3\" data-anker=\"Z8d98d30e81cf30f314ef8a92ef5d6e8e\" data-sememe-id=\"l9Yvnr\">portal vein thrombosis</a> with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LS0wZf&anker=Zd5beacd46243f9dbc75a7032728717a5\" data-learningcard-id=\"LS0wZf\" data-anker=\"Zd5beacd46243f9dbc75a7032728717a5\" data-sememe-id=\"A40RNT\">portal hypertension</a> complications. However, it is not the initial step in management.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>While some <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zf755e99eca186a2dfdaa32b290e1ba0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zf755e99eca186a2dfdaa32b290e1ba0f\" data-section-id=\"Z8cZOV0\" data-sememe-id=\"VjXGzB\">portal vein</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thromboses</span> in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=PS0W-2&anker=Za99be06553ff299396a513bb65ed71be\" data-learningcard-id=\"PS0W-2\" data-anker=\"Za99be06553ff299396a513bb65ed71be\" data-sememe-id=\"D401lT\">cirrhosis</a> may be incidental and stable, acute symptomatic <span data-sememe-id=\"eybxVw\">thrombosis</span> requires intervention. Supportive care alone risks progression to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cS0aA2&anker=Z25168aee9d4e0266b8ee7dae3d33cc08\" data-learningcard-id=\"cS0aA2\" data-anker=\"Z25168aee9d4e0266b8ee7dae3d33cc08\">intestinal ischemia</a> or worsening hepatic decompensation.</div>",
